<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 04 at 4:30PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Armstrong
and eastern Randall Counties through 500 PM CDT...
At 429 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles east of Palo Duro Canyon, or 11 miles southwest of Claude,
moving south at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Claude, Wayside and Palo Duro Canyon.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
